quizzes.question:
Fill in the blank to declare an integer variable and set its value to 5.
[!raw!]
{0} var = {1};

Fill in the blanks to print the sum of the two variables.
[!raw!]
int x = 2; int y = 4;
int result = x {0} {1};
System.out.println({2});

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Addition[/h1]

The + operator adds together two values, such as two constants, a constant and a variable, or a variable and a variable. Here are a few examples of addition: [code format="java"]int sum1 = 50 + 10; 
int sum2 = sum1 + 66; 
int sum3 = sum2 + sum2;[/code]
[h2]Subtraction[/h2]
The - operator subtracts one value from another.[code format="java"]int sum1 = 1000 - 10;
int sum2 = sum1 - 5;
int sum3 = sum1 - sum2;[/code]

quizzes.question:
What is the result of the following code?
int x = 15; int y = 4;
int result = x / y;
System.out.println(result);

quizzes.textContent:
[h1]Multiplication[/h1]

The * operator multiplies two values.[code format="java"]int sum1 = 1000 * 2;
int sum2 = sum1 * 10;
int sum3 = sum1 * sum2;[/code]
[h2]Division[/h2]
The / operator divides one value by another.[code format="java"]int sum1 = 1000 / 5;
int sum2 = sum1 / 2;
int sum3 = sum1 / sum2;[/code]
[note]In the example above, the result of the division equation will be a whole number, as [b]int [/b]is used as the data type. You can use [b]double [/b]to retrieve a value with a decimal point.[/note]

